  "texts": [
    "The defendant(s) then respond, usually with a MTD.",
    "Because of the requirements set forth in the PSLRA, many securities class actions do get dismissed.",
    "Cases may be dismissed for any of the following reasons:",
    "• Lack of jurisdiction of the court (either subject matter or personal);",
    "• Improper process or service thereof; • \"Improper venue\" (Practical Law Securities Litigation & White Collar Crime 2023); • \"Failure to state a claim\" (most commonly claimed in securities class action MTDs, as this reflects the underlying weakness of the case) (Practical Law Securities Litigation & White Collar Crime 2023); or • \"Failure to join a party\" (Practical Law Securities Litigation & White Collar Crime 2023)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}